I don't normally leave bad reviews but I was pretty disappointed with this place. I have been to other Puerto Rican restaurants in Chicago and loved them, and saw this one recommended on a blog and was excited to try it. Upon walking in, we were completely ignored by staff so we just sat down at a booth. We did not have anyone visit our table or acknowledge us and I had to go up to a waitress and ask for menus more than once. We were one of 3 groups in the restaurant so it wasn't busy. When a waitress finally came over, she tossed our menus on the table and walked away without a word. We ordered 2 appetizers and both were hard and dry, tasting like they were prepared days before. We also ordered jibaritos, which I do not recommend. The plaintains were good but the rest of the ingredients were cheap and bland. Neither of us could finish our meals, and both felt sick after. The only reason I gave this place 2 stars instead of 1 is because I do want to cut them some slack, being a small business.
